	<title>The Parliament Buildings - Peace Tower</title>
	<description>The central Peace Tower of the Canadian Parliament buildings on Parliament Hill in Ottawa. Looks as iconic as always on this beauitful day. Apparently the clock was a gift from England and installed only in 1927.. The original tower that stood here burnt down 1916 and was replaced by the current one.

&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peace_Tower&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peace_Tower&lt;/a&gt;

<photo id=\"20758424571\" secret=\"a90060d8a6\" server=\"5759\" farm=\"6\" dateuploaded=\"1440140081\" isfavorite=\"0\" license=\"4\" safety_level=\"0\" rotation=\"90\" originalsecret=\"09edcd35c1\" originalformat=\"jpg\" views=\"196\" media=\"photo\">
	<owner nsid=\"77742560@N06\" username=\"shankar s.\" realname=\"shankar s.\" location=\"Dubai, united arab emirates\" iconserver=\"457\" iconfarm=\"1\" path_alias=\"shankaronline\" />
	<title>Reminded me of the old days of steam locomotives!</title>
	<description>A stately arch leads to a chamber that is tightly closed and off limits to the public. It looked rather formidable with that solid teak door flanked by the Canada flag on either side. The dark patch at the centre over the arch top reminded me of the day of steam locomotives, where passing trains always used to leave such soot marks on bridges, tunnel entrances etc. thanks to the smoke from the steam engines! (Ottawa, Canada, June 2015)</description>
	<visibility ispublic=\"1\" isfriend=\"0\" isfamily=\"0\" />

	<title>Model of the Parliament House</title>
	<description>A model of the Canadian Parliament buildings from the 1800s, seen here displayed at the upper level of the Bytown Museum. We visited the Parliament buildings the following day. The library block with it's conical shape can be seen clearly here. Now where are the Parliament buildings in relation to the Rideau Canal? A model of the Canal itself can be seen right at the bottom (that diagonal thick grey line with those white borders- you can even see the many locks). The Bytown Museum/ Commissariat Building we are in now can be seen just above the canal at the bottom of this picture. (Ottawa, Canada, June 2015) </description>

<photo id=\"20134097091\" secret=\"47d61bace1\" server=\"3748\" farm=\"4\" dateuploaded=\"1438219409\" isfavorite=\"0\" license=\"0\" safety_level=\"0\" rotation=\"0\" views=\"80564\" media=\"photo\">
	<owner nsid=\"38880314@N07\" username=\"flashfix\" realname=\"\" location=\"\" iconserver=\"3674\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"flashfix\" />
	<title>Hot Yoga on the Hill **Explored**</title>
	<description>July 29, 2015

&lt;i&gt;&amp;quot;Yoga is a way to freedom. By its constant practice, we can free ourselves from fear, anguish and loneliness.&amp;quot; - Indra Devi&lt;/i&gt;

-----

With the temperatures hovering around 40 degrees Celsius, I was surprised to see that the heat did not keep people away from Yoga on the Hill.

While I don't think the crowd was as dense as it often is, there was still a large crowd braving the hot sun.

A weekly tradition in the summer, it seems many are dedicated, no matter the weather. 

For more information on Yoga on the Hill visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/events/826801807385483/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;their Facebook page&lt;/a&gt;.

Hope everyone has had a good day.

Click &amp;quot;L&amp;quot; for a larger view. 
</description>

<rsp stat=\"ok\">
<photo id=\"15722627434\" secret=\"01f6974cf4\" server=\"8665\" farm=\"9\" dateuploaded=\"1421983578\" isfavorite=\"0\" license=\"0\" safety_level=\"0\" rotation=\"0\" views=\"3338\" media=\"photo\">
	<owner nsid=\"38880314@N07\" username=\"flashfix\" realname=\"\" location=\"\" iconserver=\"3674\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"flashfix\" />
	<title>Provincial Lines</title>
	<description>January 22, 2015

&lt;i&gt;&amp;quot;The difference between stupidity and genius is that genius has its limits.&amp;quot; - Albert Einstein&lt;/i&gt;

------

It was another one of those fairly long days; but I did spend the majority of it away from the office. This morning took me over to Quebec and on the way back the wait time for a cab was a bit excessive so I decided to walk. 

The sun was shining and the wind was mild so it wasn't too bad and it did give me the opportunity to be outside and shoot a bit. 

Crossing over the Eddy bridge, I stopped to snap a few shots as it's a place I hadn't shot before, I wish I had been able to stop on way over to Quebec this morning when the sky was a dusty pink but was pressed for time and didn't think the cab driver would appreciate the request to pull over on a bridge, so a noon hour shot will have to do for now. 

Anyway, hope everyone has had a good day. 

Click &amp;quot;L&amp;quot; for a larger view.</description>

	<title>Major General Georges P. Vanier on the day of his inauguration as Governor General of Canada, 1959 / Le major général Georges P. Vanier lors de sa cérémonie d’entrée en fonction à titre de gouverneur général du Canada, en 1959</title>

	<title>The Parliament Buildings - Peace Tower</title>
	<description>The central Peace Tower of the Canadian Parliament buildings on Parliament Hill in Ottawa. Looks as iconic as always on this beauitful day. Apparently the clock was a gift from England and installed only in 1927.. The original tower that stood here burnt down 1916 and was replaced by the current one.

<photo id=\"20134097091\" secret=\"47d61bace1\" server=\"3748\" farm=\"4\" dateuploaded=\"1438219409\" isfavorite=\"0\" license=\"0\" safety_level=\"0\" rotation=\"0\" views=\"80564\" media=\"photo\">
	<owner nsid=\"38880314@N07\" username=\"flashfix\" realname=\"\" location=\"\" iconserver=\"3674\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"flashfix\" />
	<title>Hot Yoga on the Hill **Explored**</title>
	<description>July 29, 2015

&lt;i&gt;&amp;quot;Yoga is a way to freedom. By its constant practice, we can free ourselves from fear, anguish and loneliness.&amp;quot; - Indra Devi&lt;/i&gt;

-----

With the temperatures hovering around 40 degrees Celsius, I was surprised to see that the heat did not keep people away from Yoga on the Hill.

While I don't think the crowd was as dense as it often is, there was still a large crowd braving the hot sun.

A weekly tradition in the summer, it seems many are dedicated, no matter the weather. 

For more information on Yoga on the Hill visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/events/826801807385483/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;their Facebook page&lt;/a&gt;.

Hope everyone has had a good day.

Click &amp;quot;L&amp;quot; for a larger view.

	<description>The central Peace Tower of the Canadian Parliament buildings on Parliament Hill in Ottawa. Looks as iconic as always on this beauitful day. <photo id=\"20134097091\" secret=\"47d61bace1\" server=\"3748\" farm=\"4\" dateuploaded=\"1438219409\" isfavorite=\"0\" license=\"0\" safety_level=\"0\" rotation=\"0\" views=\"80564\" media=\"photo\">
	<owner nsid=\"38880314@N07\" username=\"flashfix\" realname=\"\" location=\"\" iconserver=\"3674\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"flashfix\" />
	<title>Hot Yoga on the Hill **Explored**</title>
	<description>July 29, 2015

&lt;i&gt;&amp;quot;Yoga is a way to freedom. By its constant practice, we can free ourselves from fear, anguish and loneliness.&amp;quot; - Indra Devi&lt;/i&gt;

-----

With the temperatures hovering around 40 degrees Celsius, I was surprised to see that the heat did not keep people away from Yoga on the Hill.

While I don't think the crowd was as dense as it often is, there was still a large crowd braving the hot sun.

A weekly tradition in the summer, it seems many are dedicated, no matter the weather. 

For more information on Yoga on the Hill visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/events/826801807385483/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;their Facebook page&lt;/a&gt;.

Hope everyone has had a good day.

Click &amp;quot;L&amp;quot; for a larger view.

	<owner nsid=\"87857621@N00\" username=\"caribb\" realname=\"Caribb\" location=\"Montreal, Canada\" iconserver=\"39\" iconfarm=\"1\" path_alias=\"caribb\" />
	<title>The Parliament Buildings - Peace Tower</title>
	<description>The central Peace Tower of the Canadian Parliament buildings on Parliament Hill in Ottawa. Looks as iconic as always on this beauitful day. Apparently the clock was a gift from England and installed only in 1927.. The original tower that stood here burnt down 1916 and was replaced by the current one.

<rsp stat=\"ok\">
<photo id=\"20134097091\" secret=\"47d61bace1\" server=\"3748\" farm=\"4\" dateuploaded=\"1438219409\" isfavorite=\"0\" license=\"0\" safety_level=\"0\" rotation=\"0\" views=\"80565\" media=\"photo\">
	<owner nsid=\"38880314@N07\" username=\"flashfix\" realname=\"\" location=\"\" iconserver=\"3674\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"flashfix\" />
	<title>Hot Yoga on the Hill **Explored**</title>
	<description>July 29, 2015

&lt;i&gt;&amp;quot;Yoga is a way to freedom. By its constant practice, we can free ourselves from fear, anguish and loneliness.&amp;quot; - Indra Devi&lt;/i&gt;

-----

With the temperatures hovering around 40 degrees Celsius, I was surprised to see that the heat did not keep people away from Yoga on the Hill.

While I don't think the crowd was as dense as it often is, there was still a large crowd braving the hot sun.

A weekly tradition in the summer, it seems many are dedicated, no matter the weather. 

For more information on Yoga on the Hill visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/events/826801807385483/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;their Facebook page&lt;/a&gt;.

Hope everyone has had a good day.

Click &amp;quot;L&amp;quot; for a larger view. 
</description>

	<description>The central Peace Tower of the Canadian Parliament buildings on Parliament Hill in Ottawa. Looks as iconic as always on this beauitful day. <photo id=\"20134097091\" secret=\"47d61bace1\" server=\"3748\" farm=\"4\" dateuploaded=\"1438219409\" isfavorite=\"0\" license=\"0\" safety_level=\"0\" rotation=\"0\" views=\"80565\" media=\"photo\">
	<owner nsid=\"38880314@N07\" username=\"flashfix\" realname=\"\" location=\"\" iconserver=\"3674\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"flashfix\" />
	<title>Hot Yoga on the Hill **Explored**</title>
	<description>July 29, 2015

&lt;i&gt;&amp;quot;Yoga is a way to freedom. By its constant practice, we can free ourselves from fear, anguish and loneliness.&amp;quot; - Indra Devi&lt;/i&gt;

-----

With the temperatures hovering around 40 degrees Celsius, I was surprised to see that the heat did not keep people away from Yoga on the Hill.

While I don't think the crowd was as dense as it often is, there was still a large crowd braving the hot sun.

A weekly tradition in the summer, it seems many are dedicated, no matter the weather. 

For more information on Yoga on the Hill visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/events/826801807385483/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;their Facebook page&lt;/a&gt;.

Hope everyone has had a good day.

Click &amp;quot;L&amp;quot; for a larger view.

	<owner nsid=\"87857621@N00\" username=\"caribb\" realname=\"Caribb\" location=\"Montreal, Canada\" iconserver=\"39\" iconfarm=\"1\" path_alias=\"caribb\" />
	<title>The Parliament Buildings - Peace Tower</title>
	<description>The central Peace Tower of the Canadian Parliament buildings on Parliament Hill in Ottawa. Looks as iconic as always on this beauitful day. Apparently the clock was a gift from England and installed only in 1927.. The original tower that stood here burnt down 1916 and was replaced by the current one.

&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peace_Tower&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peace_Tower&lt;/a&gt;

<photo id=\"20134097091\" secret=\"47d61bace1\" server=\"3748\" farm=\"4\" dateuploaded=\"1438219409\" isfavorite=\"0\" license=\"0\" safety_level=\"0\" rotation=\"0\" views=\"80565\" media=\"photo\">
	<owner nsid=\"38880314@N07\" username=\"flashfix\" realname=\"\" location=\"\" iconserver=\"3674\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"flashfix\" />
	<title>Hot Yoga on the Hill **Explored**</title>
	<description>July 29, 2015

&lt;i&gt;&amp;quot;Yoga is a way to freedom. By its constant practice, we can free ourselves from fear, anguish and loneliness.&amp;quot; - Indra Devi&lt;/i&gt;

-----

With the temperatures hovering around 40 degrees Celsius, I was surprised to see that the heat did not keep people away from Yoga on the Hill.

While I don't think the crowd was as dense as it often is, there was still a large crowd braving the hot sun.

A weekly tradition in the summer, it seems many are dedicated, no matter the weather. 

For more information on Yoga on the Hill visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/events/826801807385483/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;their Facebook page&lt;/a&gt;.

Hope everyone has had a good day.

Click &amp;quot;L&amp;quot; for a larger view.

<photo id=\"20134097091\" secret=\"47d61bace1\" server=\"3748\" farm=\"4\" dateuploaded=\"1438219409\" isfavorite=\"0\" license=\"0\" safety_level=\"0\" rotation=\"0\" views=\"80565\" media=\"photo\">
	<owner nsid=\"38880314@N07\" username=\"flashfix\" realname=\"\" location=\"\" iconserver=\"3674\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"flashfix\" />
	<title>Hot Yoga on the Hill **Explored**</title>
	<description>July 29, 2015

&lt;i&gt;&amp;quot;Yoga is a way to freedom. By its constant practice, we can free ourselves from fear, anguish and loneliness.&amp;quot; - Indra Devi&lt;/i&gt;

-----

With the temperatures hovering around 40 degrees Celsius, I was surprised to see that the heat did not keep people away from Yoga on the Hill.

While I don't think the crowd was as dense as it often is, there was still a large crowd braving the hot sun.

A weekly tradition in the summer, it seems many are dedicated, no matter the weather. 

For more information on Yoga on the Hill visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/events/826801807385483/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;their Facebook page&lt;/a&gt;.

Hope everyone has had a good day.

Click &amp;quot;L&amp;quot; for a larger view.

	<owner nsid=\"28853433@N02\" username=\"BiblioArchives / LibraryArchives\" realname=\"\" location=\"Canada\" iconserver=\"3770\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"lac-bac\" />
	<title>Fire-damaged Centre Block, Parliament Buildings, taken the day after the fire / L’édifice du Centre du Parlement, le lendemain de l’incendie qui l’a endommagé</title>
	<description>&lt;b&gt;Title / Titre :&lt;/b&gt; 
Fire-damaged Centre Block, Parliament Buildings, taken the day after the fire /

L’édifice du Centre du Parlement, le lendemain de l’incendie qui l’a endommagé

&lt;b&gt;Creator(s) / Créateur(s) : &lt;/b&gt;J.B. Reid

&lt;b&gt;Date(s) : &lt;/b&gt; February 4, 1916 / 4 février 1916

&lt;b&gt;Reference No. / Numéro de référence : &lt;/b&gt; MIKAN 3192646, 3623746
   
&lt;a href=&quot;http://collectionscanada.gc.ca/ourl/res.php?url_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;amp;url_tim=2015-07-27T15:20:21Z&amp;amp;url_ctx_fmt=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&amp;amp;rft_dat=3192646&amp;amp;rfr_id=info:sid/collectionscanada.gc.ca:pam&amp;amp;lang=eng&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;collectionscanada.gc.ca/ourl/res.php?url_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;amp;...&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;b&gt;Location / Lieu : &lt;/b&gt; Ottawa, Ontario, Canada

	<owner nsid=\"38880314@N07\" username=\"flashfix\" realname=\"\" location=\"\" iconserver=\"3674\" iconfarm=\"4\" path_alias=\"flashfix\" />
	<title>Hot Yoga on the Hill **Explored**</title>
	<description>July 29, 2015

&lt;i&gt;&amp;quot;Yoga is a way to freedom. By its constant practice, we can free ourselves from fear, anguish and loneliness.&amp;quot; - Indra Devi&lt;/i&gt;

-----

With the temperatures hovering around 40 degrees Celsius, I was surprised to see that the heat did not keep people away from Yoga on the Hill.

While I don't think the crowd was as dense as it often is, there was still a large crowd braving the hot sun.

A weekly tradition in the summer, it seems many are dedicated, no matter the weather. 

For more information on Yoga on the Hill visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/events/826801807385483/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;their Facebook page&lt;/a&gt;.

Hope everyone has had a good day.

Click &amp;quot;L&amp;quot; for a larger view. 
</description>
